The evidence with the title 'High-speed rail in the United States - Wikipedia ' says Plans for high-speed rail in the United States date back to the High Speed Ground Transportation Act of 1965 . Various state and federal proposals have followed . Despite being one of the world's first countries to get high-speed trains ( the Metroliner service in 1969), it failed to spread.  ... .. U.S. federal and state governments continued to revisit the idea of fast trains . 
